lab1a.c : C source code that performs duplex terminal I/O, processes communication, changing terminal modes
	  and supports a --shell option that creates another process to run shell commands from input terminal

Makefile: default: compile lab1a.c with -Wall and -Wextra options
	  clean: removed executable file, and .tar.gz
	  dist: zip tarball containing lab1a.c, Makefile, README

reference Sources:
set up noncanonical mode  - https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Noncanon-Example.html
using poll multiplexing - http://www.unixguide.net/unix/programming/2.1.2.shtml
fork example - https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/fork-system-call/
pipe system call - https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/pipe-system-call/
Termios - https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/007904875/functions/tcgetattr.html
